article.description: Marcel White and Kori Babineaux scored 17 points apiece to help Jacksonville beat Florida Memorial 92-73 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Jacksonville beats Florida Memorial 92-73
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Marcel White and Kori Babineaux scored 17 points apiece to help Jacksonville beat Florida Memorial 92-73 on Wednesday night. Jacksonville made 11 3-pointers with four each from Darius Dawkins and White. Dawkins finished with 14 points for Jacksonville (3-5). Josh Adeyeye added two 3s and scored 10 points. Dawkins made three 3-pointers in the first four minutes of the second half for a 13-point advantage and the Dolphins led by at least nine points the rest of the way. Andre Braziel led Florida Memorial, a NAIA Division II member, with 19 points on five makes from distance. Aluk Adub added 16 points. Florida Memorial did not make a field goal over the final six minutes of the first half and Jacksonville closed on a 10-2 run for a 37-25 lead.
